Longest Repeating Subsequence
Difficulty: MediumAccuracy: 48.54%Submissions: 147K+Points: 4Average Time: 20m
Given string str, find the length of the longest repeating subsequence such that it can be found twice in
the given string.

The two identified subsequences A and B can use the same ith character from string s if and only if
that ith character has different indices in A and B. For example, A = "xax" and B = "xax" then the
index of the first "x" must be different in the original string for A and B.